observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to instruct the concerned officials to:

• observe strict compliance with the revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 regarding conduct of competitive bidding;
• scrutinize thoroughly the legality, technicality and validity of the submitted documents;
• justify the deficiencies in the procurement of the project and absences of the documents mentioned;
• strictly adhere to the DPWH standards relative to the project being implemented;
• comply firmly to the stipulations mentioned in the CSHP; and
• adhere strictly with the reportorial and posting requirements under DILG MC No. 2019-71.

We recommended and Management agreed to instruct the concerned officials to –
maintain supplies ledger cards and stock cards, containing the details for each receipts, issuances and remaining balances of all supplies;
use moving average method as basis for the costing of supplies;
submit the summary of supplies and materials issued regularly to the Accounting Office for proper accounting thereof; and
assign additional personnel to the Accounting Office who will assist in the preparation of the necessary records and reconciliation with the GSO.

We recommended and Management agreed to instruct the concerned officials to:
observe strict compliance with the revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 regarding conduct of competitive bidding;
scrutinize thoroughly the legality, technicality and validity of the submitted documents;
justify the deficiencies in the procurement of the project and absences of the documents mentioned;
strictly adhere to the DPWH standards relative to the project being implemented;
comply firmly to the stipulations mentioned in the CSHP;
adhere strictly with the reportorial and posting requirements under DILG MC No. 2019-71;
revert the unutilized funds to the Bureau of Treasury; and
study the provisions of the guidelines before implementing the project.

We recommended that the LCE instruct the concerned officials to – 

submit the lacking documents required under RA 9184 and COA 2012-001 immediately; 
submit the approved copy of the contracts and the documents forming part thereof within the prescribed period as required under Item 3.1 of the COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009;
justify the deficiencies noted in the procurement of the project; 
comply with the reportorial and posting requirements under DILG MC No. 2018-61; and


analyze the provisions of the guidelines or MOA before implementing the project.
